The paper focuses on using deep learning methods for source code analysis, specifically for classifying security-relevant commits. This falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with transfer learning and adapting a state-of-the-art approach to represent source changes, which could also be relevant to the categories of cryptography and security (cs.CR), machine learning (cs.LG), programming languages (cs.PL), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
